Questions that arise after the accident: Are stewards in the bus illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long distance bus is forbidden
In the context of the tragic accident of the bus company Student Agency near Padua, Italy, the question arises whether stewards and passengers can travel within the bus during the journey.
"If the law is to be strictly and formally respected, the activity of a steward is contrary to the road traffic law," said the spokesman for the Ministry of Transport Karel Hanzelka.
The accident in question, during which a 22-year-old hostess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck that crossed the bus path.
The girl was, unfortunately, sitting next to the driver in the most dangerous seat of the vehicle, although she had two other seats at her disposal.
However, the coach may have an accident or even suddenly brake, also when the steward serves the coffee or distributes the newspapers.
What matters is whether the bus is under its technical specification equipped with standing or not seats.
If this standing seating equipment is not approved, passengers must remain seated.
The long distance buses Student Agency do not have standing seats; this was confirmed in Aktuálně.cz by the director of the company Radim Jančura.
"This is a matter that we discussed with the Department and, at first, it prohibits any movement of passengers.
Then they cancelled it and we got that passengers can go to the toilet during the ride provided they have their own seat," he revealed his position.
The law ignores stewards
"There is no one-size-fits-all legal interpretation of the role of steward - no legal requirement deals with this role.
On the other hand, no legal requirement also prohibits the carrier from offering services.
The law on road transport knows only the term of vehicle receiver; it does not define its rights and duties," added the spokesman, Hanzelka, more ambiguously.
Josef Pokorný, director of the Road Traffic Department, believes, on the contrary, that the law sufficiently addresses the issue.
"It all depends on whether the coach has permission in its approval to offer standing seats.
Everything resides in it," he says.
The buses are divided into urban ones, where there are standing places and a limited maximum speed, tolls with standing places and a higher permissible speed and long distance buses without standing places with the highest permissible maximum speed and seats equipped with safety belts.
As on the plane, says an expert
Jaroslav Hořín, expert at BESIP (road traffic safety) in transport safety, does not see the movement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"In regular traffic, there is no danger. The situation can be compared to that of service in aircraft.
Nor is it safe when turbulence occurs and the hostess of the air can hit her head."
"But in the event that the bus would have stopped abruptly, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
In the same way as on an urban bus or tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of stewards by means of internal requirements," he says and also believes that from the point of view of the law, the problem is not solved.
Jančura is ready to delete these services
Student Agency is the only bus carrier to offer steward services.
He's hiring two hundred.
Even after this accident, the director does not consider their profession to be a risky one.
"However, as soon as I get the impression that it's a risky trade, I'll delete it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and newspaper at boarding.
It would also reduce costs," he said.
The safety concern is the reason given to the absence of stewards in his vehicles by the director of the Asiana Alexei Litvine, who ensures, in comparison with SA, a very small number of lines.
"We don't have a hostess, we've been opposed from the beginning.
Sooner or later this will end in a fatal accident," he said, a year ago, at Týden.cz.
A huge tragedy has arrived
A young hostess from the Plzeň region, who had been working for the company for two years, died during the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably left the emergency stop strip without using a flasher and blocked the way to the bus.
The driver of the latter tried to avoid it by means of a sudden maneuver, but he strove on his right side.
Jančura refuses that the two seats reserved for the stewards' rest were sold.
"In the case of long distance lines, it is not possible to reserve these places, they are blocked."
The company intends to file a complaint against the truck driver.
For the compensation of the girl's family, the agency will not wait for the court's judgment, but with regard to financial compensation, it also relies on the culprit.
An amendment to the law?
Not in view
An amendment to the Act, which has been being prepared for more than a year by a group of thirty experts from the Ministry of Transport, could provide details on the journey of stewards on board the coach.
"But it did not come to any conclusion on this point.
In fact, she is not too interested in buses, but rather in the point system, the maximum speed on the motorway and the use of the mobile at the wheel," said expert Hořín.
"The Ministry of Transport does not consider stewards' activity to be something that would fundamentally endanger passenger safety," concludes Spokesman Hanzelka, stating that the control of the safety of buses is under the authority of the police and the Office for Safety at Work.
