Alcohol would avoid this because it is a system connected to the vehicle that measures the alcohol level in the breath and prevents the vehicle from starting if the driver does not blow before; or when the alcohol level of the driver is higher than that allowed.
Its cost is more than 1,000 euros and is at the driver's expense.
In this regard, a study conducted in the United States in 2007 showed that vehicles equipped with this device reduced up to 65% of the infringements in the first year of installation.
And in Spain it is estimated that this could save 115 people every year.
This measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: dealing with these behaviours before they become criminal offences.
