The marina of Quiberon was also blocked, but connections to Belle-isle did not stop.
A filter dam was set up on the Quiberon peninsula.
The sailors have already shown their determination on Monday by burning, at dawn, tires and pallets in front of the fuel deposits of the ports of Brest, and Lorient, while demonstrations were taking place in Concarneau or Saint-Brieuc.
The movement has spread to other ports of the Atlantic front and the Channel, as in the Sables d'Olonne, in Vendée, where the trawlers have remained at dock, or in the Havre, where about twenty ships have blocked the movements of the commercial ships.
The fishermen of La Turballe and the Croisic, in the Loire-Atlantique, stopped in the evening the blockade of the important Total refinery of Donges.
Those in Boulogne-sur-Mer decided to wait until Wednesday's meeting at the Ministry to decide on possible actions.
In the Guilvinec, the "crisis committee" must decide on Tuesday the follow-up to the movement and its participation in the interview planned at the Ministry of Agriculture and Fisheries in Paris.
But some Breton fishermen do not want to be represented by officials of the National Fisheries Committee, who did not support their movement.
"The strike will continue" because "fishers will not let go" and "don't want to move to Paris", for example announced Liliane Cariou, president of the Lorient Fisheries Committee.
