The reason may also be that geeks see very exactly the problematic relationship between human rights and the internet, and what web 2.0, the most proclaimed keyword of recent years, is right behind it.
Indeed, web 2.0 does not concern anything other than collaboration, that the fact that we intentionally leave traces behind us, and that we use channels of communication made available to us, and while the dimension of these changes one by one, the essential remains the same: we expose ourselves.
