The one who lives an online life is made up of what he shows of himself, and that is how one can define the principle hiding behind the behavior of today's young people.
He wants to hide something, or at least he wants to try to circumvent Google's monopoly, can do so (starting, for example, with Scroogle, using Google's search system, but at the same time, intentionally leaving no trace).
The number of people who deliberately do not register on public pages so that it is not possible to find them is not the least. Google's services online, through the processing of text to image processing, to the reading of information can be replaced by alternative versions, which are not attached to huge server parks and which do not assemble our best profile, having existed to date.
Public opinion is waiting, without really hiding it, for Google to reveal its true nature.
