Today, the European Summit for Equal Opportunities, hosted by France, began in Paris as a representative of the current Presidency of the European Union.
In his message to the plenary assembly, as one of the main spokespersons for the consultation of experts, Livia Járóka, MEP Fidesz European People's Party, drew attention to segregation in education, because it is a violation of the law that most affects Roma children and therefore one of the main obstacles to their success in life.
