"Because of the country's debt and the increase in the trade deficit, the collapse of social security, 'evoking the silence of a cemetery', is now only a matter of time," Milinkevich says.
Unlike the opposition politician, Russian observers have described the elections as democratic.
Sergei Lebedev, leader of the mission of the Commonwealth of Independent States, told Russian news agency Ria Novosti: "People do not believe in words, but in deeds." In this way, the absence of opposition is only proof of the maturity of Belarusian voters.
